      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "160657a0-02a4-45ee-abff-d88fdb310957",
        "lesson_activity.key": "95b57443-3696-49c6-bfc3-001aa3ab9497"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "78e0e406-bc6c-4b6f-9426-afaf0cc2d8b3",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:**  *What made your campaign compelling and actionable? What could be improved to make it even more effective?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:**  Students recognize strengths and areas for improvement in their campaigns while connecting their work to real-world advocacy strategies.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "78e0e406-bc6c-4b6f-9426-afaf0cc2d8b3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "95b57443-3696-49c6-bfc3-001aa3ab9497"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7600b2b6-434f-4931-87de-c363da5a2532",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:**  Click through the animated slides to display the prompts.\n- *What is one aspect of your advocacy campaign that you are most confident about so far?*\n- *What is one part of your campaign that could still be clarified, improved, or polished?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:**  Students build confidence in their campaigns by highlighting strengths and what is working well so far. They also have an opportunity to think critically about their campaign’s weaker points in order to develop a plan for improvement.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7600b2b6-434f-4931-87de-c363da5a2532",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f2905ad7-7f17-432a-8379-e2c5beef01e3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7a781bea-13b4-478b-a2af-6b63535866a6",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Direct students to review their campaign using the key criteria (clear argument, strong evidence, actionable solutions). Remind them to check and refine their materials so they are presentation-ready. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  Ensure students are making intentional revisions rather than just small tweaks. Ask guiding questions like, “How does your campaign persuade your audience?” and “Are your solutions realistic and well-supported?” Provide quick feedback on clarity and presentation.",
        "duration": "30",
        "name": "Activity",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Consider setting a timer to help students stay focused. You may want to give a five-minute warning before the final check-in so they can wrap up any last details."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7a781bea-13b4-478b-a2af-6b63535866a6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f2905ad7-7f17-432a-8379-e2c5beef01e3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "218384fd-d4e2-4b4e-92c9-b936b8ec87c3",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "218384fd-d4e2-4b4e-92c9-b936b8ec87c3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f2905ad7-7f17-432a-8379-e2c5beef01e3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "278c72c8-3c48-4b1d-aa80-4cc493e40028",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:**  Give each student several copies of the Peer Feedback Cards.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Instruct groups to pair up with another group. Group A presents while Group B listens and records feedback. After each group has presented, they will pair up with another group and repeat the process.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  Ensure presenters stay focused and listeners engage with feedback. Encourage students to ask questions and provide specific, constructive feedback. Support groups by clarifying ideas and keeping discussions on track."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "278c72c8-3c48-4b1d-aa80-4cc493e40028",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f2905ad7-7f17-432a-8379-e2c5beef01e3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3d63d2ef-ccaf-4015-9de1-8eb8846bab2b",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Direct students to complete the End of Project Reflection in their Project Planning Guide as well as on Code Studio, Level 1. If time allows, you can have students share their responses with a partner or do a whole class share-out.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Project Planning Guide and group’s final format of their campaign pitch can be collected and used to formatively assess the lesson objectives:\n- Explain the role of routers, switches, and servers in ensuring the Internet is reliable and can grow.\n- Propose actionable solutions to address key societal impacts of the digital divide and net neutrality\n- Propose AI-driven solutions to improve Internet access and address challenges like the digital divide."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3d63d2ef-ccaf-4015-9de1-8eb8846bab2b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f2905ad7-7f17-432a-8379-e2c5beef01e3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "97350086-b379-475b-b6ef-2e13c0e9988f",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Final Project Reflection"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "97350086-b379-475b-b6ef-2e13c0e9988f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f2905ad7-7f17-432a-8379-e2c5beef01e3"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0a706855-9999-4d1d-8044-fdec2cdefde9",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:** Show the video \"How Cyber Attacks Happen in Real Life\".",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "To encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Y-kGl_pc2afuSBKhKkdulu53X50mc7T-RQZA4vGLpY4/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0a706855-9999-4d1d-8044-fdec2cdefde9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3092b527-c401-4d27-8cc0-8c04f4faa10a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0d47d503-53c6-4a76-a66c-df996331e94a",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0d47d503-53c6-4a76-a66c-df996331e94a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3092b527-c401-4d27-8cc0-8c04f4faa10a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fcfb0b21-1ad6-4e9f-806b-4ea611fa271b",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What vulnerabilities allowed the hacker to breach Acme Corporation’s network?*\n- *What could Acme have done to prevent the attack?*\n- *What impact did the attack have on Acme, and how do you think it could impact their customers?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students recognize that multiple security failures—including weak passwords, social engineering, and multi-factor authentication (MFA) fatigue—enabled the hacker to breach Acme Corporation’s network. Guide students to identify how better security practices, such as stronger password policies, improved multi-factor authentication, and offline backups, could have prevented the attack. Encourage students to consider the broader consequences, including financial loss, reputational damage, and compromised customer data.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fcfb0b21-1ad6-4e9f-806b-4ea611fa271b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3092b527-c401-4d27-8cc0-8c04f4faa10a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4e2c0217-f89b-427b-ad42-4c83a61e623d",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Place students in pairs or small groups of three. Make sure students have their Unit Guide out and opened to Lesson 9.",
        "name": "Network Defense",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Identify, Defend, Reflect! activity is an interactive game in which students will use a clickable slideshow that will navigate them through various network vulnerabilities. The goals of the activity are to:\n- Discover common network vulnerabilities\n- Investigate key details of those vulnerabilities\n- Identify appropriate defenses in network vulnerability scenarios\n\nThe game is covers four common network vulnerabilities. Each should take about 7 minutes to complete. We recommend modeling the first vulnerability to demonstrate how to interact with the slideshow."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4e2c0217-f89b-427b-ad42-4c83a61e623d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0a99c4b-d66a-4b4b-b810-e587bb84950a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4a028c7c-255d-4152-a5a6-a1d4558c72cd",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4a028c7c-255d-4152-a5a6-a1d4558c72cd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0a99c4b-d66a-4b4b-b810-e587bb84950a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "43227d09-07fb-449f-8e1a-9a2ddb6e8bd8",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the four key security threats students will encounter in the simulation.\n\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Walk students through the sample notes. Point out what kind of info goes in each column, emphasizing quick notes and ideas they might want to return to later. "
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "43227d09-07fb-449f-8e1a-9a2ddb6e8bd8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0a99c4b-d66a-4b4b-b810-e587bb84950a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8675e5e7-d70d-4f03-b813-41e55fd1e1eb",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Today, you'll step into the role of a cybersecurity analyst, investigating real-world security threats and deciding how to defend against them. Follow the instructions in the interactive slide deck, record your observations in your Unit Guide, and think critically about how to protect networks from cyber attacks",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8675e5e7-d70d-4f03-b813-41e55fd1e1eb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0a99c4b-d66a-4b4b-b810-e587bb84950a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "840093ab-0bcb-40b6-baa4-afde280837b7",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 9, Level 1. Lead the class through a demonstration of the first “round” of the interactive slide show. Walk them through one scenario and model how to navigate through the slides and record notes in the unit guide. Then, release students to work with their partners to complete the remaining scenarios. ",
        "progression_name": "Identify, Defend, Reflect!"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "840093ab-0bcb-40b6-baa4-afde280837b7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0a99c4b-d66a-4b4b-b810-e587bb84950a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "32ec9013-afb8-44ec-aa48-58f17c295c06",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As students work through the slides, check that students are following the instructions and recording observations. Listen for discussions between partners—are they just clicking through, or are they analyzing the scenarios. When students are selecting defenses, ask probing questions about what made them choose certain options.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *If you were a cybersecurity analyst for Cybershield Inc., which mitigation strategy would you prioritize implementing first, and why?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students think critically about the mitigation strategies they encountered in the interactive slideshow. They discuss the importance of a variety of mitigation strategies and the consequences of not having those strategies in place.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 9, Level 2 to complete the Check for Understanding.",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "32ec9013-afb8-44ec-aa48-58f17c295c06",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0a99c4b-d66a-4b4b-b810-e587bb84950a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c31d608b-c824-46c1-9aab-d7b4e6cef4dc",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c31d608b-c824-46c1-9aab-d7b4e6cef4dc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0a99c4b-d66a-4b4b-b810-e587bb84950a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5fabdae7-f481-4182-b0e1-e6eb8318d3a4",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Give students a quick minute to jot down their thoughts on the Question of the Day. Encourage students to include at least one specific example from any of today’s activities.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Question of the Day effectively assesses the lesson objectives if students provide responses that explain:\n- common network security vulnerabilities.\n- solutions to mitigate security risks."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5fabdae7-f481-4182-b0e1-e6eb8318d3a4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5c8de525-deb7-4304-828c-4732984a9c3c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "85795e72-f5c2-446c-9af1-3a2f6d100d4d",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "85795e72-f5c2-446c-9af1-3a2f6d100d4d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5c8de525-deb7-4304-828c-4732984a9c3c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bc2e61b4-a846-4735-bbd3-ec0bcd82bb63",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Label the four corners of the room: Phishing, Weak Passwords, Social Engineering, Default Credentials. Instruct students to go to the corner that relates to the one vulnerability they mentioned in their question of the day answer. Have students share their answers and compare mitigation strategies. If time allows, have one person from each group share one takeaway from their discussion with the class.\n",
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bc2e61b4-a846-4735-bbd3-ec0bcd82bb63",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5c8de525-deb7-4304-828c-4732984a9c3c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5bf10247-c1ad-47e8-9e38-c0b7e4470a67",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:**  Show the video “AI-Based, Real-Time Threat Detection” to students. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How does detecting threats in real time improve network security compared to delayed detection? What challenges might companies face when adopting AI-driven security tools like Morpheus? How could these challenges be addressed?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:**This discussion prepares students to think critically about the role of AI in modern cybersecurity and its real-world applications. Students analyze how real-time threat detection improves network security, contrasting AI-driven tools with traditional methods that often detect threats too late. Encourage students to consider how faster detection helps prevent breaches and limits damage. Guide them to recognize the challenges organizations face when implementing AI security tools, such as cost, training, or false positives, and how these barriers can be addressed.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ensure students are making connections between AI’s strengths and challenges. Ask questions like,*“What happens if AI misidentifies a threat?”*or*“Why might some organizations be hesitant to rely on AI security tools?”*"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5bf10247-c1ad-47e8-9e38-c0b7e4470a67",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4f1ed2a9-7280-44da-9a6c-d40252f4a5db"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0c342574-d907-4904-a5a0-ea4bfc8ca6ac",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0c342574-d907-4904-a5a0-ea4bfc8ca6ac",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4f1ed2a9-7280-44da-9a6c-d40252f4a5db"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c3aa00b1-1e41-41a3-a462-aabf512b7e24",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain to students that today, they are diving into one of the most cutting-edge topics in cybersecurity—how AI is revolutionizing network security. Every second, massive amounts of data are moving through networks, and cyber threats are evolving just as quickly. Traditional security methods struggle to keep up, but AI is changing the game by detecting threats in real time before they cause damage. As they explore AI-driven security tools today, encourage students to think critically about whether AI is the ultimate solution, or does it have its own risks and challenges.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c3aa00b1-1e41-41a3-a462-aabf512b7e24",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4f1ed2a9-7280-44da-9a6c-d40252f4a5db"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3b756ce8-ba44-4bc3-953d-282976fb3598",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Put students into groups of two.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:**  Give each pair of students a copy of the Threat Detected! Cards and the AI Threat Detection Notetaker activity guide.",
        "name": "AI Threat Detection",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "For early finishers or advanced groups, provide a set of Tier Two Threat Detected! Cards. These cards introduce more complex or ambiguous scenarios that require deeper analysis of AI limitations, ethical concerns, and the need for human oversight. Encourage students to use the same notetaker and apply their learning from earlier rounds."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3b756ce8-ba44-4bc3-953d-282976fb3598",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ad01a3d2-0531-41dd-9498-aaf27ab46c13",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ad01a3d2-0531-41dd-9498-aaf27ab46c13",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a0abe456-d0d4-429d-a378-433e07cbb4be",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Today, you will act as security analysts, using an AI threat detection system to investigate and respond to security threats. Your goal is to evaluate how AI-based security tools work compared to traditional detection methods. Work with your partner to complete this activity. You will receive one set of AI Threat Detection Cards and you will each have your own Threat Detection Notetaker to fill out individually.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a0abe456-d0d4-429d-a378-433e07cbb4be",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ce630b4b-f4b3-4b67-9b8d-1328b855c9bf",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain that students will act as security analysts interacting with an AI threat detection system to analyze and respond to network vulnerabilities. Review the steps for drawing a Threat Detected card, discussing the scenario with the AI Chatbot, recording the results of the discussion on the Activity Guide, and then drawing a new card to repeat the process.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 10, Level 1 to interact with the threat detection chatbot and complete their activity guide. ",
        "progression_name": "Threat Detection Chatbot"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ce630b4b-f4b3-4b67-9b8d-1328b855c9bf",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d1684afc-4a1b-468a-b57f-eaf3d0cebf6a",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Give students at least 20 minutes to complete as many threat cards as possible in that time. Then, direct student to move on to Level 2 to complete a check for understanding. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  Circulate and listen for students who assume AI is always accurate. If students trust the AI’s responses without question, ask: ‘Could AI ever misidentify a threat? How would that impact security?’ Ensure students also consider limitations like false positives, AI bias, and the need for human oversight.",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, display anonymous student responses for the check for understanding on Level 2 and go over misconceptions or ask students what similarities and differences they notice about the responses."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "Level 2 can be used to formatively assess the learning objectives."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d1684afc-4a1b-468a-b57f-eaf3d0cebf6a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "832f9efe-6e38-4b9e-a746-63cf9c5ed6c2",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "832f9efe-6e38-4b9e-a746-63cf9c5ed6c2",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4a58d3d6-94d1-4397-984c-a221506d24ba",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Show the model threat detection notes, emphasizing short, clear notes instead of full sentences. Remind students that they don’t need to capture every word from the chatbot, just the gist of its response.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Put students into groups of four. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Instruct students to choose one scenario from their activity and discuss with their group what the AI got right, where it needed human support, and what surprised them about how the AI handled the threat.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  Encourage students to move beyond ‘AI is faster’ as their key argument. Ask: ‘Does AI replace human analysts completely? What tasks might still require human decision-making?’ Look for responses that mention AI’s adaptability, scalability, and data processing power while recognizing that human oversight is still necessary.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:**  Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What patterns did you notice in AI’s responses to each threat?*\n- *How did AI improve security compared to traditional methods?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:**  Students analyze patterns in AI’s responses to security threats and evaluate its strengths and weaknesses. Encourage them to consider what AI does well (speed, data analysis, automation) and where it struggles (bias, detecting new types of threats, false positives). Guide them to recognize that AI is a tool, not a replacement for human decision-making in cybersecurity.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain to students that the next slides will have a statement about AI and cybersecurity. Students will hold a thumbs up for True, thumbs down for False, or thumbs sideways for unsure. Once students have held up their answer, you will reveal the correct answer and explain why.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the slide and ask students to choose whether it’s true or false. Once students have indicated their answer, move onto the next slide to reveal and discuss.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain why the statement is false: AI is powerful, but it’s not perfect—some scams still slip through. Hackers continuously adapt their methods, and AI can sometimes generate false positives or miss subtle attacks. Human judgement should be the first line of defense. Remind students that if they are unsure whether something is a scam, take a step back and cross-check with a trusted source, like speaking to the person who sent the message in person.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the slide and ask students to choose whether it’s true or false. Once students have indicated their answer, move onto the next slide to reveal and discuss.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain why the statement is false: Social engineering works because it looks convincing—attackers impersonate real people, use familiar logos, and create a sense of urgency. Remind students to always examine the sender details, such as looking to see if the email address matches the school or company’s domain. Other ways you can tell are any red flags, like urgent requests, odd grammar, or messages that ask for personal information.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the slide and ask students to choose whether it’s true or false. Once students have indicated their answer, move onto the next slide to reveal and discuss.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain why the statement is false: Even responding to a scam email can be dangerous—attackers confirm active accounts based on responses and might target students again. Remind students that when in doubt, use this approach: ‘STOP-THINK-VERIFY’ before interacting with any suspicious message. Never respond to a message with any personal information before verifying that it is actually the person they say they are. The best way to do this is to ask the person in real life."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4a58d3d6-94d1-4397-984c-a221506d24ba",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9aab8fb8-102e-40e6-aac9-2b5c99c261cd",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9aab8fb8-102e-40e6-aac9-2b5c99c261cd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "77a5a451-a808-4854-a0ca-200eed9f3922"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8728ebc1-415d-4cec-a8bf-627b03b1a316",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Review the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students take out their The Fabric of the Internet and AI Unit Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Place students in pairs or small groups of three.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to briefly share their thoughts about what makes AI effective at enhancing network security and how it compares to traditional methods before individually writing their own response to the Question of the Day in their Unit Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Encourage students to go beyond basic thoughts such as “it’s faster” by making connections to today’s activities."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Question of the Day effectively assesses the lesson objectives if students provide responses that explain:\n- the role of AI in real-time threat detection.\n- An example of AI-based solutions to network security challenges."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8728ebc1-415d-4cec-a8bf-627b03b1a316",
        "lesson_activity.key": "983cb8ee-f120-41e1-85e7-80fa2f578f9e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "aea1005d-8273-486a-9a9c-744b2c18b138",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "aea1005d-8273-486a-9a9c-744b2c18b138",
        "lesson_activity.key": "983cb8ee-f120-41e1-85e7-80fa2f578f9e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ca570571-d2b0-41be-aee5-8719310a7034",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**How do we create a network security risk assessment?**"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ca570571-d2b0-41be-aee5-8719310a7034",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2d24cea2-d384-4fba-a9e6-cda4623e8757"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "afe263b0-4a28-4ee1-b9e5-d2b1f280d3af",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.*What vulnerabilities would you look for first, and why? \nHow might these weaknesses affect the company if exploited?*\n- *What vulnerabilities would you look for first, and why?*\n- *How might these weaknesses affect the company if exploited?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should explore both technical and human vulnerabilities, considering how cybercriminals exploit weak security measures. Guide students to discuss the real-world impact of these breaches on businesses and individuals, including financial loss, reputational damage, and privacy concerns.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "afe263b0-4a28-4ee1-b9e5-d2b1f280d3af",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2d24cea2-d384-4fba-a9e6-cda4623e8757"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1f55de24-4966-4e22-a8db-288947a0e979",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:**  Give each student a copy of the Network Security Risk Assessment Project Planning Guide. This will guide them through all three days of the project.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain to students that for the next three days, they will work as network security analysts. This means they will select a company scenario, identify vulnerabilities, assess their societal and ethical impacts, and propose both traditional and AI-driven solutions. Along the way, they will refine their recommendations through peer review.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to explain the project requirements and answer any questions.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the project rubric and hold on to any questions they may have.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What do you notice about the project rubric?*\n- *What does success look like for this project?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the tasks they will need to complete for this project.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Walk through the first example to model what quality assessment looks like for Critical Vulnerabilities and how it connects to the rubric.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Walk through the example of societal / ethical impact risk assessment to model what quality work looks like and how it connects to the rubric.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Walk through the example of critical vulnerabilities risk assessment to model what quality work looks like and how it connects to the rubric.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to introduce the steps students will take on Day 1.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to introduce the steps students will take on Day 2.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to introduce the steps students will take on Day 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Direct students to Lesson 11, Level 1 to choose a company scenario. Instruct them to complete the graphic organizer on their Project Planning Guide for their chosen company. ",
        "duration": "30",
        "name": "Activity",
        "progression_name": "Company Case Study Choices"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1f55de24-4966-4e22-a8db-288947a0e979",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2d24cea2-d384-4fba-a9e6-cda4623e8757"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9d68f704-cc46-454f-90e4-8b46e28a7de8",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  As students identify vulnerabilities, check that they are categorizing them correctly (technical, human, systemic). If students list general risks, ask: ‘How does this vulnerability actually lead to a security breach?’ Encourage deeper thinking by asking: ‘What would happen if this vulnerability were exploited? Who would be affected?'\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What types of vulnerabilities came up the most?*\n- *Which ones do you think pose the biggest risks, and why?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should identify patterns in network vulnerabilities across different scenarios and evaluate which pose the most significant risks. Guide them to justify their reasoning using examples, considering which vulnerabilities are most easily exploited, which have the greatest impact, and which are hardest to mitigate."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9d68f704-cc46-454f-90e4-8b46e28a7de8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2d24cea2-d384-4fba-a9e6-cda4623e8757"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "88ffd82b-df1f-407f-8750-7c11efbea2fb",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How do we create a network security risk assessment?*\n- Use the Modified Whip Around protocol to facilitate this discussion.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students explain the key components of a Network Security Risk Assessment, including examples from their own learning from the day’s lesson.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Modified Whip Around Protocol:\n- Individually: Students answer the Question of the Day in 1-2 sentences.\n- Small Groups: Students share their responses in groups of 4.\n- Whole-Class: 2-3 groups are called on to share key insights or common patterns from their discussion."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "88ffd82b-df1f-407f-8750-7c11efbea2fb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2d24cea2-d384-4fba-a9e6-cda4623e8757"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "90b2d372-8e97-4bc6-9eca-29aa6715ec0c",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "90b2d372-8e97-4bc6-9eca-29aa6715ec0c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2d24cea2-d384-4fba-a9e6-cda4623e8757"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bcced4a3-b41f-4ba4-864f-db247b4098e6",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**How can we ensure our security recommendations are effective?**"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bcced4a3-b41f-4ba4-864f-db247b4098e6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3844b094-e3f9-42c1-a644-a79fe4740bd0",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What kind of assistance would you hope AI could provide?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Activate prior knowledge by encouraging students to brainstorm potential AI applications in cybersecurity before being introduced to specific AI-driven solutions.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3844b094-e3f9-42c1-a644-a79fe4740bd0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "51f27ef0-5549-4f4f-adff-b8b582832f8d",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to review the steps students will take on Day 2.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Display the steps students will take as they engage with the AI chatbots to explore how AI is transforming cybersecurity, engaging with specialized AI chatbots to see how these tools detect threats, respond to attacks, and protect networks. Remind students to think about how these AI-driven solutions could strengthen the security recommendations in your risk assessment project as they interact with the chatbots.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Direct students to Lesson 11, Level 2 to learn about four possible AI-driven solutions to network vulnerabilities. ",
        "duration": "30",
        "name": "Activity",
        "progression_name": "AI-Driven Solution Chatbots"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "51f27ef0-5549-4f4f-adff-b8b582832f8d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ef312cf5-7e75-44c3-96e9-767c30c5344f",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate**: Listen for misconceptions that AI eliminates the need for human oversight. Ask: ‘Would this AI tool catch every security threat? Why or why not?’ If students struggle to connect AI to specific vulnerabilities, prompt them to revisit their case study and ask: ‘How would this AI solution specifically help prevent or detect this threat?’",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If students struggle with chatbot responses, model how to rephrase questions for clarity and specificity."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ef312cf5-7e75-44c3-96e9-767c30c5344f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f034dae2-a987-4c9d-8980-f166145f626f",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f034dae2-a987-4c9d-8980-f166145f626f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "672ae23c-fbf1-456c-a895-ebb5f9329967",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Describe each of the AI-Driven solutions and ask students to connect a tool to their company’s biggest risk."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "672ae23c-fbf1-456c-a895-ebb5f9329967",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "dcfe490f-7a59-48fc-b453-75092aaf59a0",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Direct students to begin drafting their Network Security Risk Assessment using their Project Planning Guide. Encourage students to focus on clear, specific details about their chosen scenario, vulnerabilities, mitigation strategies, and societal impacts.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As students are working, check for depth and specificity—are they identifying vulnerabilities with enough detail? Ask questions like: “How does this vulnerability affect the company and its customers?” Guide students struggling with AI solutions by prompting: \"Which AI-driven strategy fits best with this risk? Why?\" Redirect students who list solutions without explanation by asking: “How does this mitigation strategy actually reduce the risk?”",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If students are stuck, have them partner up briefly to explain their vulnerabilities out loud—verbal processing often helps refine ideas."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "- Use this draft to gauge students' understanding of network vulnerabilities and AI-driven solution and to provide quick feedback and positive reinforcement.\n- As you review student’s work, look for:\n   - Clear and specific scenario and risks\n   - Thoughtful categorization of vulnerabilities\n   - Feasible and well-explained mitigation strategies\n   - Ethical/societal impact that goes beyond surface-level thinking"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "dcfe490f-7a59-48fc-b453-75092aaf59a0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5065a5ad-33c4-43fd-a7e9-d9bdd5e7f4b1",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5065a5ad-33c4-43fd-a7e9-d9bdd5e7f4b1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fad7a8fb-028b-458b-a2b6-f3a8f45ac896",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:**  *How can AI enhance network security?*\n- Use the Modified Whip Around protocol to facilitate this discussion.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should evaluate how AI-driven security tools improve threat detection and mitigation. Encourage them to compare AI’s capabilities to traditional security methods and consider how AI can support (but not replace) human decision-making in cybersecurity. Guide students to connect these insights to real-world applications in their risk assessments.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Wrap Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fad7a8fb-028b-458b-a2b6-f3a8f45ac896",
        "lesson_activity.key": "64bd139e-9ba7-4485-bbd6-7e5f52533644"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5e8cc1c8-6e03-41a4-bc2c-7a5486e9e1ee",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**What makes a network risk assessment thorough and actionable?**"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5e8cc1c8-6e03-41a4-bc2c-7a5486e9e1ee",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5b475bc0-3257-49d8-9ab2-7fca121b9937"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ef7afea2-5c11-4890-9806-92f405c9064a",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:**  Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What have you learned?*\n- *How has your understanding of network vulnerabilities and solutions changed?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:**  Students reflect on their learning by identifying key takeaways about network vulnerabilities, the consequences of those vulnerabilities, mitigation strategies, and AI-driven solutions.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ef7afea2-5c11-4890-9806-92f405c9064a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5b475bc0-3257-49d8-9ab2-7fca121b9937"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e702285d-5224-4efa-8fed-d7e112de8465",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Put students into groups of two to conduct peer reviews. Either assign peer-review partners or direct students to find a partner and exchange drafts. Remind them to use their Project Planning Guide to structure their feedback, making sure it is specific and constructive.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  As students work, check that both partners are giving and receiving feedback. To ensure students are engaged and on-task, ask probing questions :*“What’s one suggestion you’ve given your partner to improve their assessment?”*Listen for specific feedback, not just “this looks good” or “I agree.” Redirect with:*“Can you explain why this solution is effective or suggest an alternative?”*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Direct students to navigate to Lesson 11, Level 3 in order to complete their final Network Security Risk Assessment. Once students have finished, make sure that they prepare a 30-second oral summary to share with a classmate.",
        "duration": "30",
        "name": "Activity",
        "progression_name": "Final Risk Assessment"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e702285d-5224-4efa-8fed-d7e112de8465",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5b475bc0-3257-49d8-9ab2-7fca121b9937"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a784b21e-2c1a-4e92-a0ac-95ea118bb7b1",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Divide students into two equal groups and arrange them into two lines, facing each other. Explain the students that they will take turns delivering a 30-second summary of their project and receiving feedback from the peer they are facing. Direct students to use the prompts on the screen to guide their responses if needed, and listen carefully to your partner’s insights. After 5 minutes, they will switch roles. After both pairs have shared, one line will rotate down and they will share again with a new partner.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Consider modeling a strong 30-second summary before students begin, demonstrating concise and clear communication, and reiterating the need to answer the displayed prompts. If students struggle to stay within time limits, use a visual or auditory timer to keep rounds on track. Encourage students to ask follow-up questions rather than just saying “good job” (e.g., “How does your solution compare to real-world cases?”)."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "These presentations can serve as an informal formative assessment opportunity. As students talk, check for the following: \n- Are students addressing all key prompts?\n- Do they provide specific details rather than vague answers?\n- Are they engaging with feedback and refining their explanations?"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a784b21e-2c1a-4e92-a0ac-95ea118bb7b1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5b475bc0-3257-49d8-9ab2-7fca121b9937"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "728291d2-1aaf-43e9-a9b7-799730ddd7ae",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "728291d2-1aaf-43e9-a9b7-799730ddd7ae",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5b475bc0-3257-49d8-9ab2-7fca121b9937"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "506f4fe1-4b0e-4998-8374-14b97e8dcd3b",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "After completing this project, students should complete the End of Unit Survey linked in the final level. Their responses help us understand their experiences and improve future versions of this unit.",
        "progression_name": "End of Unit Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
